The paper deals with the Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP) on graphs, which is a classic problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on cubic and subcubic graphs, which are types of graphs with specific properties. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also uses polyhedral techniques, which are related to linear programming, so cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization and approximation algorithms, which could fall under cs.OC (Operations Research).
